HEADWORD: Cocklebur
<hw>Coc"kle*bur`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A coarse, composite weed, having a rough or prickly fruit; one of
several species of the genus <gen>Xanthium</gen>; -- called also
<altname>clotbur</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cockled</ent>⟦br⟧
